Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp; rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.181, 8. Name Aristokles. Not obviously a piece known from extant material.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0812)
